<paragraph id="IAS36_132" base="SL32354" principles="no"><paranum>132</paranum><prolog><data name="standard_number" value="IASÂ 36"/><data name="paranum" value="132"/></prolog><body><p id="IAS36_P0442">An entity is encouraged to disclose assumptions used to determine the <xref base="SL148458" href="IAS36_6.dita#IAS36_6/IAS36_P0106">recoverable amount<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0319"/></ph></xref> of assets (<xref base="SL148451" href="IAS36_6.dita#IAS36_6/IAS36_P0096">cash&#x2011;generating units<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0031"/></ph></xref>) during the period. However, <xref id="IAS36_X0363" base="A36-260" href="IAS36_134.dita#IAS36_134">paragraph 134</xref> requires an entity to disclose information about the estimates used to measure the recoverable amount of a cash&#x2011;generating unit when goodwill or an intangible asset with an indefinite <xref base="SL148459" href="IAS36_6.dita#IAS36_6/IAS36_P0109">useful life<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0380"/></ph></xref>  is included in the <xref base="SL148450" href="IAS36_6.dita#IAS36_6/IAS36_P0095">carrying amount<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0026"/></ph></xref> of that unit.</p></body></paragraph>